===Definitions===
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# {{lb|zh|literary}} to [[follow]] (e.g. a tradition)
#: {{zh-co|因循守舊|to adhere to tradition}}
# {{lb|zh|literary}} to [[take]] [[advantage]]; to [[make use of]] a situation
#* {{zh-x|^孔-父{fǔ} ^嘉 為{wéi} 司馬，^督 為{wéi} 大{tài}-宰，故 因 民 之 不堪 命，先 宣言 曰「司馬 則 然。」|(At the time) Kongfu Jia was the Marshal and Hua Du the Chancellor. Therefore the latter, '''making use of''' popular resentment (against frequent drafts), first spread the words that it was the Marshal that accented their suffering.|ref=Zuozhuan}}
#* {{zh-x|於 ^柯 之 會，^桓-公 欲 背 ^曹 ^沫 之 約，^管 ^仲 因 而 信 之。|At the Convention of Ke, {{w|Duke Huan of Qi|Duke Huan}} wanted to renege on his oath with Cao Mo. Yet {{w|Guan Zhong}}, '''taking advantage''' of the situation, greatly amplified the Duke's reputation of trustworthiness.|ref=Shiji}}
# {{lb|zh|archaic}} [[conveniently]]; [[in passing]]; [[expediently]]
#* {{zh-x|今 人 有 大功 而 擊-之，不義 也，不如 因 善 遇-之。|It is beneath ourselves to attack a person because of his merit. We had better, '''as a matter of convenience''', treat him with goodwill.|ref=Shiji}}
# {{lb|zh|archaic}} [[thus]]; [[in]] [[such]] [[way]]; [[therefore]]; [[accordingly]]
#* {{zh-x|初 欲 棄 之，因 名 曰 ^棄。|She wanted to abandon the infant at first, and '''thus''' named him "Qi", the abandoned one.|ref=Shiji}}
# {{lb|zh|archaic}} [[through]]; [[via]]
#* {{zh-x|^衛 ^鞅 聞 是 令 下，西 入 ^秦，因 ^景-監 求 見 ^孝-公。|{{w|Shang Yang|Yang of Wey}}, on hearing the decree's promulgation, left westward for Qin and sought the audience of {{w|Duke Xiao of Qin|Duke Xiao}} '''through''' the eunuch Jing.|ref=Shiji}}
# {{lb|zh|obsolete}} to [[multiply]]
#* {{zh-x|令 兩 出-門 步-數 相{xiāng}乘{chéng}，因 而 四 之，為{wéi} 實。開方 除 之，即 得 邑 方。|Multiply the two distances to the respective portals, and '''multiply''' that product by four to obtain the quadruple as the operand. Take the square root of the operand, and one finds the side-length of the square equiareal to the rectangular town.|CL|ref={{circa2|2nd century {{BCE}}|short=yes}}, ''{{w|Nine Chapters on the Mathematical Art}}'' ({{lang|zh|《九章算術》}})}}
#* {{zh-x|以 六 因 之，得 一 丈 二 尺。|'''Multiply''' that number by six, and one obtains one ''zhang'' and two ''chi''.|CL|ref={{circa2|5th century|short=yes}}, ''{{w|Sunzi Suanjing}}'' ({{lang|zh|《孫子算經》}})}}
# [[depend]]ing on; [[according to]]; [[base on|based on]]; [[contingent]] upon
#: {{zh-co|因人而異|to vary from one person to another}}
#: {{zh-co|因地制宜|to make plans '''according to''' local conditions}}
#* {{zh-x|若 因 過去 時，有 未來 現在：未來 及 現在，應{yīng} 在 過去 時。|If the present and the future were '''contingent on''' the past, then the present and the future would have existed in the past.|CL|ref={{circa2|409|short=yes}}, {{w|Kumārajīva}} ({{lw|zh|鳩摩羅什}}), translator. The ''{{w|Mūlamadhyamakakārikā}}'' by {{w|Nāgārjuna}} ({{lang|zh|《[[w:zh:中論|中論]]》}}). English text based on [http://www2.hf.uio.no/common/apps/permlink/permlink.php?app=polyglotta&context=record&uid=0884f19a-6be5-11df-870c-00215aecadea the translation] by Stephen Batchellor.}}
# {{lb|zh|Cantonese}} to [[estimate]]
#: {{zh-x|你 因 下{haa5} 啲 時間{gaan3}，睇 下{haa5} 要 幾 耐 先 到。|'''Estimate''' the time to see how long it takes to arrive.|C}}
